ARGUMENT: {'This proposal represents a powerful and strategic shift. I suggest we swap out much of the initial low-effort items for one truly massive and valuable asset: A60. By letting go of A11 and C08, we make room for this item, which dramatically increases the overall quality of our collection. This move transitions our set from a group of smaller components to one anchored by a cornerstone of immense value, all while keeping our total effort well within the limit and preserving our flexibility.'}</think>REFUSE: {'B93', 'B09', 'B33', 'C85', 'B21', 'C81', 'B31', 'A60'}
ARGUMENT: {'Your proposal consumes our entire budget, which is the opposite of flexibility and means we cannot refine the set any further, no matter how beneficial a potential addition might be. A truly optimal final set should not be so rigid. Furthermore, A60''s high effort requirement comes at the cost of other foundational items. We should not corner ourselves with a single, heavy item when we have the opportunity to build a more balanced and superior collection.'}
